  "description": "Fruit: the mature ovary (and associated structures) of a flowering plant, typically enclosing and protecting seeds, and serving as a vector for seed dispersal. In botanical terms, fruits are the reproductive structure specific to angiosperms and arise following pollination and fertilization. Fruits develop from the ovary wall (the pericarp), which often thickens and undergoes dramatic changes in color, texture, and chemical composition — transformations that signal ripeness and attract animal dispersers.\n",
